Mr Changawa is currently vying for the seat on a Movement for Democracy and Growth (MDG) party ticket following his defeat by ODM’s Dickson Karani during the party’s primaries.
Mr Karani contested the 2017 election at the High Court, a move that led to the nullification of the exercise and an order for a fresh vote to take place.
Baya's claims
Trouble started on Tuesday after Kilifi North MP Owen Baya claimed, after voting at Dabaso Primary School, that ODM had deployed goons in four Land Cruisers to intimidate voters.



