Speaking to the press, Mr Baya said they would not allow ODM members to intimidate their candidate and called on security forces to do their work effectively .
“We have reports of ODM members intimidating people with a view to keeping them away from polling stations. We shall not allow it,” he said.
Mr Baya claimed the goons focused on Mr Changawa’s strongholds in order to keep his supporters from voting.
"The ODM goons invaded a shop at the Rising Sun Primary School polling centre and looted food because it is owned by a person who does not support ODM," he said.
He did not give proof to support his allegations.
Other allegations
Later, three women led by former MCA Barke Mohamed, who is also the Kilifi County Women’s League chair, stood outside the Dabaso polling station, saying they were there to check on their agents.



