Police officers stepped in as youths began picking up sticks, apparently to use them to attack Ms Mohamed and her two colleagues, after Mr Baya asked them to clear crowds outside the polling center.
At the Mijomboni Primary School polling station, ODM Youth Coordinator Nyundo Samir almost clashed with Mr Abdulrahman Omar, a former Ganda MCA, who is supporting Mr Changawa.
Mr Samir accused the former MCA of being among those who were dishing out money to people in order for them to vote for Mr Changawa.
“We have heard of people dishing out money. If we find them they will regret it,” he said.
He advised the people to return home after voting and wait there for the outcome of the election to be announced.
On his part, Mr Omar claimed ODM ferried 30 vehicles, among them two buses, full of goons from Kilifi and Nairobi to intimidate and harass voters.
Mr Hillary Kombe, the Dabaso Ward Returning Officer, said the ward has 12,620 voters, registered at 22 polling stations spread across 10 polling centres. DP Ruto's allies have accused security officers of siding with their rivals in ODM and letting them bribe and intimidate voters. The constituency has been without a member of Parliament since March following the death of Suleiman Dori The Uganda Communications Commission says the channels were used to mobilise riots in November that resulted in many deaths. Residents report seeing SNA troops taking strategic positions along the border. Kenyan Uber drivers say their investments have gone down the drain.